# Subagent Dispatch

When Left or Right need to dispatch a subagent:

**Load the appropriate agent prompt from `.cursor/agents/`** — each agent has its own file.

## Dispatch via mcp_task

Use `mcp_task` with the correct `subagent_type`:

| Agent | subagent_type |
|-------|--------------|
| Developer | `developer` |
| Reviewer | `reviewer` |
| Planner | `planner` |
| Left | `orchestrator-left` (Dispatcher only) |
| Right | `orchestrator-right` (Dispatcher only) |

## Terminal / Command Execution (Lite)

This lite version does not define a dedicated `shell` / Terminal subagent.
However, `developer` and `reviewer` MAY execute test commands using the available Cursor command execution capability (as an instrument).

